class_description: This class is used to represent a ZIP file entry.

Methods.method_description: Creates a new zip entry with the specified name.

Creates a new zip entry with fields taken from the specified
 zip entry.
Returns a copy of this entry.

return_description: the comment string for the entry, or null if none

Methods.method_description:
Returns the comment string for the entry.
See also:

return_description: the size of the compressed entry data, or -1 if not known

Methods.method_description:
Returns the size of the compressed entry data.

 
 In the case of a stored entry, the compressed size will be the same
 as the uncompressed size of the entry.
See also:

return_description:
the CRC-32 checksum of the uncompressed entry data, or -1 if
 not known

Methods.method_description:
Returns the CRC-32 checksum of the uncompressed entry data.
See also:

return_description: the creation time of the entry, null if not specified

Methods.method_description:
Returns the creation time of the entry.

 
 The creation time is from the extended timestamp fields of
 entry's optional extra data when read from a ZIP file
 or ZIP file formatted stream.
See also:

return_description: the extra field data for the entry, or null if none

Methods.method_description:
Returns the extra field data for the entry.
See also:

return_description: The last access time of the entry, null if not specified

Methods.method_description:
Returns the last access time of the entry.

 
 The last access time is from the extended timestamp fields
 of entry's optional extra data when read from a ZIP file
 or ZIP file formatted stream.
See also:

return_description: The last modification time of the entry, null if not specified

Methods.method_description:
Returns the last modification time of the entry.

 
 If the entry is read from a ZIP file or ZIP file formatted
 input stream, this is the last modification time from the zip
 file entry's optional extra data if the extended timestamp
 fields are present. Otherwise the last modification time is read
 from the entry's date and time fields, the default TimeZone is used to convert
 the standard MS-DOS formatted date and time to the epoch time.
See also:

return_description: the compression method of the entry, or -1 if not specified

Methods.method_description:
Returns the compression method of the entry.
See also:
Returns the name of the entry.

return_description: the uncompressed size of the entry data, or -1 if not known

Methods.method_description:
Returns the uncompressed size of the entry data.
See also:

return_description:
The last modification time of the entry in milliseconds
          since the epoch, or -1 if not specified

Methods.method_description:
Returns the last modification time of the entry.

 
 If the entry is read from a ZIP file or ZIP file formatted
 input stream, this is the last modification time from the date and time fields of the zip file entry. The
 default TimeZone is used
 to convert the standard MS-DOS formatted date and time to the
 epoch time.
See also:

return_description: a hash code value for this object.

Methods.method_description: Returns the hash code value for this entry.

return_description: true if this is a directory entry

Methods.method_description:
Returns true if this is a directory entry. A directory entry is
 defined to be one whose name ends with a '/'.

Sets the optional comment string for the entry.

 
ZIP entry comments have maximum length of 0xffff. If the length of the
 specified comment string is greater than 0xFFFF bytes after encoding, only
 the first 0xFFFF bytes are output to the ZIP file entry.
See also:

params.param_description: the compressed size to set to

Methods.method_description:
Sets the size of the compressed entry data.
See also:

Sets the CRC-32 checksum of the uncompressed entry data.
See also:

params.param_description: The creation time of the entry

Methods.method_description:
Sets the creation time of the entry.

 
 If set, the creation time will be stored into the extended
 timestamp fields of entry's optional extra data, when
 output to a ZIP file or ZIP file formatted stream.
See also:

Sets the optional extra field data for the entry.

 
 Invoking this method may change this entry's last modification
 time, last access time and creation time, if the extra field
 data includes the extensible timestamp fields, such as NTFS tag
 0x0001 or Info-ZIP Extended Timestamp, as specified in
 Info-ZIP
 Application Note 970311.
See also:

params.param_description: The last access time of the entry

Methods.method_description:
Sets the last access time of the entry.

 
 If set, the last access time will be stored into the extended
 timestamp fields of entry's optional extra data, when output
 to a ZIP file or ZIP file formatted stream.
See also:

params.param_description: The last modification time of the entry

Methods.method_description:
Sets the last modification time of the entry.

 
 When output to a ZIP file or ZIP file formatted output stream
 the last modification time set by this method will be stored into
 zip file entry's date and time fields in standard
 MS-DOS date and time format), and the extended timestamp fields
 in optional extra data in UTC time.
See also:

params.param_description: the compression method, either STORED or DEFLATED

Methods.method_description:
Sets the compression method for the entry.
See also:

Sets the uncompressed size of the entry data.
See also:

params.param_description:
The last modification time of the entry in milliseconds
         since the epoch

Methods.method_description:
Sets the last modification time of the entry.

 
 If the entry is output to a ZIP file or ZIP file formatted
 output stream the last modification time set by this method will
 be stored into the date and time fields of the zip file
 entry and encoded in standard MS-DOS date and time format.
 The default TimeZone is
 used to convert the epoch time to the MS-DOS data and time.
See also:

return_description: a string representation of the object.

Methods.method_description: Returns a string representation of the ZIP entry.
